            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Technically you could onion-route arbitrary data via DHT, but it makes no sense for Tox to do so. Tox aims to establish direct connection between the recipient and the sender to allow low-latency audio/video conferencing, high-bandwidth file transfers, etc. Anonymity is not a goal of Tox. See https://toktok.ltd/spec.html#non-goals\r\n\r\nOnion routing is currently used to solve a privacy issue with friend finding, because without the friend finding being onion-routed, one could easily learn Tox IDs of all friends any Tox ID has in their friend list. There are some proposals that promise private friend finding without needing the onion routing, so in the future the onion routing might not even be a part of Tox.",
